<body>
    <h1>Fall of Constantinople</h1>
    <div>
        <p>
           The <b>fall of Constantinople</b>, also known as the <b>conquest of Constantinople</b>, was the capture of the capital of the Byzantine Empire by the Ottoman Empire.<br>
           The city was captured on 29 May 1453 as part of the culmination of a 53-day siege which had begun on 6 April.
        </p>
        <p>
            The attacking Ottoman Army, which significantly outnumbered Constantinople's defenders, was commanded by the 21-year-old Sultan Mehmed II (later nicknamed "the Conqueror"), <br>
            while the Byzantine army was led by Emperor Constantine XI Palaiologos. After conquering the city, Mehmed II made Constantinople the new Ottoman capital, replacing Adrianople.
        </p>
    </div>
